						               													<description>A print'n play, pit and peebles inspired African themed game. During the medieval times, kingdoms and empires rise and fall in the African continent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of the game is simple, it uses a mancala/oware/awele style mechanic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a player, take control of one of the four kingdoms, rise, expand, and collect resources before falling.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will do so using a &amp;quot;pit and pebbles&amp;quot; gaming mechanic, sowing your cubes and harvesting with the last cube you sow.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will also use cubes from new comers (Europeans, Chinese, Persians, Arabs...) as Africa become a land of conquest. &amp;#10;You can sow and harvest player cubes with these cubes, but you can't harvest new comers' cubes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So new comers will slowly gain control of the land as players use them, and players' kingdoms will fall.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game, when there are no more players cubes, the winner is the player who has harvested the most cubes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is for 2-4 players, from 6 y.o. The board is language independent, rules are in French, soon in English.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
